# InlineValidationMessage

Error validation and messaging displays when a user enters incorrect information or the system does something unexpected.
This visual and interactive element can be activated with components or in implementation and API errors.

**Validations** work in conjunction with inputs such as text fields, checkboxes, and radio buttons. When a user enters data into a form, inline validations provide feedback to the user and helps guide them to provide valid inputs. By default, inputs are required unless indicated with an “(optional)” label.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/inline-validation-message
```

```tsx
import { InlineValidationMessage } from '@ids-ts/inline-validation-message';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `automationId` | `string` | No | - |
| `id` | `string` | No | ID property |
| `message` | `string` | No | message property |
| `description` | `string` | No | description property |
| `type` | `InlineValidationType` | No | - |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface InlineValidationMessageProps
  extends Omit<ThemeableElement<'span'>, 'onChange' | 'onBlur'> {
  /**
   * AutomationID property
   *
   * @default idsInlineValidationMessage
   */
  automationId?: string;
  /** ID property */
  id?: string;
  /** message property */
  message?: string;
  /** description property */
  description?: string;
  /**
   * Determines the type of Validation Message : ['error', 'warning', 'success', 'invalid', 'info']
   *
   * @default ''
   */
  type?: InlineValidationType;
}

export type InlineValidationType =
  | 'error'
  | 'warning'
  | 'success'
  | 'invalid'
  | 'info'
  | '';
```

</details>

